parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission hesitates or slips
the vehicle loses power
the transmission makes a loud noise
the vehicle stalls
the wrench light or transmission error code is displayed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ETB can cause the vehicle to accelerate or decelerate unexpectedly, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates or decelerates unexpectedly
the throttle control system warning light is displayed
the vehicle hesitates or stalls
the engine RPM surges or drops.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the PCM can cause the vehicle to stall, hesitate, or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls
hesitates
or loses power
the check engine light or PCM error code is displayed
the transmission slips or hesitates
the engine RPM surges or drops.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Clutch Master Cylinder or Concentric Slave Cylinder Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch master cylinder or concentric slave cylinder can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle body can cause the vehicle to surge or accelerate unexpectedly, leading to accidents or loss of control. Additionally, the vehicle may enter into fail-safe mode, causing it to stall or lose power, which can also lead to accidents or strand the driver.
symptoms: The vehicle surges or accelerates unexpectedly
the vehicle enters into fail-safe mode
the engine light illuminates
the vehicle stalls or loses power
the throttle body sensor needs to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch hydraulic system can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the concentric slave cylinder can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.
